```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return lowercase(replace(String(col), r"[^a-zA-Z\d_]" => ""))
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to ensure the column name is lowercased, `replace` with a regular expression (`r"[^a-Z0-9_]"`) to remove any characters that are not letters or digits, and then wraps the entire string in `String` to convert it back into a mutable string before stripping non-alphanumeric characters. The `\d` in the regex matches any single digit, and `_` is the underscore character.
